/*! \page ddMd_integrator_NptIntegrator_page NptIntegrator

\section ddMd_integrator_NptIntegrator_overview_sec Synopsis

NptIntegrator implements a reversible NPT (constant pressure, constant
pressure) integrator. See class documentation for further details, an
explanation of modes of operation, and a literature reference.

\sa DdMd::NptIntegrator

\section ddMd_integrator_NptIntegrator_param_sec Parameters

The parameter file format is:
\code
  NptIntegrator{ 
    dt                 double
    tauT               double
    tauP               double
    mode               Simp::LatticeSystem
  }
\endcode
in which
<table>
  <tr> 
     <td> dt </td>
     <td> time step </td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
     <td> tauT </td>
     <td> relaxation time for temperature </td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
     <td> tauP </td>
     <td> relaxation time for pressure </td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
     <td> mode </td>
     <td> Determines number of independent dimensions. Can take values
          "Cubic", "Tetragonal" or "Orthorhombic". </td>
  </tr>
</table>
See the DdMd::NptIntegrator class documentation for further discussion
of the mode parameter.

*/

}
